RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH-EN:
Carlo Botrugno has PhD in Bioethics by University of Bologna (2016), Bachelor in Social Work by University of Bologna (2012), Master in Law by University of Bologna (2008), Bachelor in Legal Sciences by University of Bologna (2005).
He currently co-coordinates the Research Unit on Everyday Bioethics and Ethics of Science (RUEBES) at L'Altro Diritto Interuniversity Research Center, Department of Legal Sciences, University of Florence, where he also works as postdoctoral fellow.
He takes part to the activities of the Experimental Research Laboratory on Bioethics and Ethics of Science (LAPEBEC) directed by Prof. Dr. José Roberto Goldim at Porto Alegre Clinicas Hospital (HCPA). His current interests of research are related to three different areas:
- Bioethics and Biolaw (right to health, inequalities and access to healthcare, technological innovation in healthcare, telemedicine and e-Health);
- International Migrations, Human Rights, and marginalisation (sociology of migration, human rights, migrations in Mediterranean area, borders control);
- Philosophy and Sociology of Law.
